//Operations:


//1. Arithmetic Operator :  Basic math operations
    //   +, -, *, %, /

//2. Assignment Operators : Used to assign values to variables
    //a. simple assignment ----> =
    //b. Compound assignment ----> +=, -=, *=, %=, /=

//3. Relational Operators(Comparison Operators) : Used to return boolean result
    //   ==, !=, >, <, >=, <=

//4. Logical Operators : Used to combine or modify boolean statements
    //   &&, ||, !

//5. Unary Operators : Operate on a single Operand
    //   +, -, ++, --, !

//6. Ternary Operators (Conditional) : a shorthand for if-then-else
    //   condition ? expression1 : expression2

//7. Bitwise Operator (Used to perform Operations at bit level)
    //    &(AND), |(Inclusive OR), ^(Exclusive OR), ~(Bitwise Complement), <<(Signed Left Shift), >>(Signed Right Shift), >>>(Unsigned Right Shift)

//* instanceof Operator (to check if an object is an instance of a particular class or interface)